Eskom announced on Wednesday morning that it will be
implementing Stage 2 loadsheding between 10 pm and 5 am on Wednesday night and
again on Thursday night. The power utility said the loadshedding is necessary in
order to recover and preserve the emergency generation reserves that have been
utilised to support the system during the week following the earlier than
planned shutdown of Koeberg Unit 1 and other unites whose return to service has
been delated. “We currently have 6 672MW on planned maintenance, while
another 12 073MW of capacity is unavailable die to unplanned maintenance. Eskom
teams are working around the clock to return as many of these units to service
as soon as possible,” said Eskom.